description.narrative: Policy advocacy efforts aimed at increased resource allocation for MNCH, improved quality of care and stronger protection measures from iodine deficiency disorders. The first ever national child nutrition report was produced based on the administrative data collection system. Health personnel in 4 regions gained knowledge and skills and were provided with standardized tools for universal progressive home visiting.
